00:07:39.710 --> 00:07:42.781
deep six entire
relationships you have.

00:07:42.781 --> 00:07:44.280
It's important to
think a little bit

00:07:44.280 --> 00:07:46.890
about what technology policy is.

00:07:46.890 --> 00:07:49.190
The basic way to say
it is it's the rules

00:07:49.190 --> 00:07:53.330
that we set about technology,
and it's not just laws.

00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:56.160
If you have two small kids
arguing over a very large piece

00:07:56.160 --> 00:07:58.739
of cake, you can set up
a really easy experiment

00:07:58.739 --> 00:08:01.030
because they both have the
interest of getting the most

00:08:01.030 --> 00:08:03.470
cake, where one cuts and
the other gets to choose it.

00:08:03.470 --> 00:08:05.980
And that is essentially
aligning incentives

00:08:05.980 --> 00:08:08.541
to get the best outcome,
the outcome being both kids

00:08:08.541 --> 00:08:10.290
are somewhat convinced
that they're happy,

00:08:10.290 --> 00:08:12.892
and they participated
in the process,

00:08:12.892 --> 00:08:14.100
so they know what's going on.

00:08:14.100 --> 00:08:16.280
But it's not just sort
of social outcomes.

00:08:16.280 --> 00:08:19.110
It's also technical, so to
what extent do the things

00:08:19.110 --> 00:08:21.620
we do result in better
things happening,

00:08:21.620 --> 00:08:25.200
better technology being
able to exist and thriving.

00:08:25.200 --> 00:08:27.450
And economic interests,
to what extent

00:08:27.450 --> 00:08:30.750
does it help the country,
and other countries,

00:08:30.750 --> 00:08:33.870
sort of build
innovative products

00:08:33.870 --> 00:08:36.380
and employ people
and things like that?

00:08:36.380 --> 00:08:38.699
This can mean that certain
things are prohibited

00:08:38.699 --> 00:08:40.240
when you make rules
about technology,

00:08:40.240 --> 00:08:41.823
and if you're a
technologist-- I don't

00:08:41.823 --> 00:08:45.960
know how many of you in the room
are, but maybe a lot of you.

00:08:45.960 --> 00:08:48.340
Technologists can often be
frustrated when someone tells

00:08:48.340 --> 00:08:50.360
them, oh, you can't do
that, and so for example,

00:08:50.360 --> 00:08:53.670
you cannot currently take
satellite imagery that is lower

00:08:53.670 --> 00:08:56.487
than about 50 centimeter
resolution, at least in the US.

00:08:56.487 --> 00:08:58.570
If you're a US company,
you cannot put a satellite

00:08:58.570 --> 00:09:00.260
in the air and then sell
the products that come out

00:09:00.260 --> 00:09:01.150
the other end.

00:09:01.150 --> 00:09:03.460
That means you guys at
Google can't actually

00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:04.935
use products that
have things that

00:09:04.935 --> 00:09:06.500
are lower than that resolution.

00:09:06.500 --> 00:09:08.640
There's currently a
company, Globalize,

00:09:08.640 --> 00:09:10.284
